phase2.explanation:
Putting implementation in headers causes slow compilation and larger binaries.

**The fix:**
```cpp
// player.h — only declarations
class Player {
public:
    void display();
};

// player.cpp — implementation
#include "player.h"
#include <iostream>
void Player::display() {
    std::cout << "Display" << std::endl;
}
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"Headers for declarations. Source files for definitions. Keep them separate."

